  "text": "Profilin is randomly distributed in pulp and peel and it is labile to heat denaturation and pepsin digestion [CITATION_1] . So it is unable to cause sensitization via the gastrointestinal tract. In fact, the ingestion of raw fruits in profilin sensitized patients usually determines reactions restricted to the oral cavity (oral allergy syndrome -OAS), despite in the literature systemic, reactions to zucchini and litches are reported [CITATION_2] .",
